<title>SOUTH AFRICA: Rooiberg details quarterly results.</title>
<headline>Rooiberg details quarterly results.</headline>
<dateline>JOHANNESBURG 1997-05-08</dateline>
<text>
<p>Quarter ended March 31 vs quarter ended November 30, 1996</p>
<p>			(million rand unless stated)</p>
<p>    Attrib income	    3.86 gain  vs   0.32 loss</p>
<p>    Pre-tax		    5.03	 vs   0.09</p>
<p>    Tax			  1.17	 vs   0.42</p>
<p>    Cost of sales	   18.22	 vs   0.39</p>
<p>    Total sales	     22.41	 vs   0.10</p>
<p>    Capex			1.14	 vs   0.02</p>
<p>    Tons milled (t)	 22.61	 vs   nil</p>
<p>    - zinc (t)		 3.43	 vs   nil</p>
<p>    - copper (t)	     0.42	 vs   nil</p>
<p>Full name: Rooiberg Tin Ltd</p>
<p>NOTE - The report is based on the assumption that the acquisition of Maranda Mining Company (Pty) Ltd will be approved at a shareholders meeting on May 12.</p>
<p>Both Rooiberg and Maranda have changed year ends to June 30 and the results incorporate a four-month period for Rooiberg and a three-month period for Maranda.</p>
<p>The listing of new Maranda shares on the Johannesburg Stock Exchange is scheduled for May 14 and a first dividend payment in August.</p>
<p>-- Johannesburg newsroom +27 11 482 1003</p>
